title: Skate Tales - The Story Of Double-Amputee Pro Skater Felipe Nunes (S2E4)
description:
Felipe Nunes is a 22-year old skater from Curitiba in Brazil. Aged just six, he lost both legs while playing on train tracks. 

After five years in a wheelchair, he was given a longboard to get around on. That longboard would become a skateboard- and the rest is history. In a short space of time he was competing in and winning contests against all-comers within his native Brazil.

People began to notice just how talented he really was. Aged eighteen, Felipe felt ready to make it beyond Brazil and started a social media fund to enter Tampa Am. Tony Hawk championed his cause, and Felipe was headed to Florida. 

Incredibly, he made the Semi’s, and finished 21st overall as the only adaptive skater in the contest! Felipe had the skateboarding world’s attention, and soon joined Tony’s brand Birdhouse Skateboards. 
In 2019, he scored the cover of Thrasher magazine and did The Loop, second go.

Now pro for Birdhouse Skateboards, his career has gone from strength to strength. 

Skate Tales is all about the skateboarding stories you don’t hear- as the man himself says: no excuses!

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Felipe Nunes é um skatista brasileiro de 22 anos de Curitiba, capital do estado do Paraná. Com seis anos de idade, ele perdeu as duas pernas enquanto brincava nos trilhos do trem.

Depois de cinco anos em uma cadeira de rodas, ele recebeu um longboard para se locomover. Aquele longboard se tornaria um skate - e o resto é história. Em um curto espaço de tempo, ele estava competindo e vencendo todos os adversários em campeonatos no Brasil.

As pessoas começaram a notar o talento gigantesco do skatista. Aos 18 anos, Felipe se sentiu pronto para ir além do Brasil e criou um crowdfunding para ir ao Tampa Am. Tony Hawk engajou na sua causa, e Felipe foi até a Flórida.

Incrivelmente, ele chegou até as Semis, e terminou em 21º colocado como o único atleta de skate adaptado no torneio! Felipe chamou a atenção do mundo do skate, e rapidamente se juntou à marca de Tony, Birdhouse Skateboards. Em 2019, ele estampou a capa da revista Trasher e fez o famoso The Loop na segunda tentativa.

Agora um "pro" pela Birdhouse Skateboards, sua carreira tem ficado cada vez mais sólida.

Skate Tales é sobre as histórias não contadas do skate - como o próprio diz: sem desculpas!

description: From those born into it, to those locked out from it, those who moved to be part of it and those hiding from it, Outliers represents a cast of skateboarders from diverse geographical backgrounds and demonstrates how their proximity to skateboarding’s epicenter has affected the way they skate.

title: Monster Children/Nike SB - Eight & Sand
description:
Eight & Sand 
Presented by Monster Children and Nike SB 
Directed by Riley Blakeway
Starring Daryl Angel and Nick Boserio
Shot entirely on Kodak 16MM Film
For issue 45 of Monster Children, Nike SB and MC put Daryl Angel and Nick Boserio on an Amtrak train and sent them up the west coast of America, from San Diego to Seattle, hunting out spots and eating fireside beans right out of the can. Filmmaker Riley Blakeway was there to document the journey.
